About Me

I have always been a tech nerd. I have built my first website at the age of 10 using Dreamweaver. After much debate between pursuing an Economics or a Computer Science major, I opted for the former. However, more than 10 years later, the interest in ‘building’ never faded. This ultimately led me to leave my job in management consulting to start at a new career in a tech company (albeit In a non-engineering role). Within the past year at Google. I have improved my SQL skills and learned Python in my spare time. After a friend introduced me to Techladies, I unhesitantly signed up for the 3 pre-bootcamp sessions. Each session further reinvigorated my love for code.
